                            <comment id="17954866" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 29 May 2025 07:05:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you be more precise such as put together a sample project ready to run. Also mind that Camel has upgraded the HTTP client between the 2 versions. Check the upgrade guides also for details&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://camel.apache.org/manual/camel-4x-upgrade-guide.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://camel.apache.org/manual/camel-4x-upgrade-guide.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17954872" author="JIRAUSER309457" created="Thu, 29 May 2025 07:55:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have checked the user guide for 4.6 to 4.11 and nothing is mentioned for camel-http component changes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we are setting the headers and its values in java dsl&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;Exchange.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0000c0&quot;&gt;HTTP_METHOD (GET)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Exchange.&lt;font color=&quot;#0000c0&quot;&gt;HTTP_URI (schema://&amp;lt;actual-hostname&amp;gt;)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Exchange.&lt;font color=&quot;#0000c0&quot;&gt;HTTP_PATH (path of the endpoint to hit)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Exchange.&lt;font color=&quot;#0000c0&quot;&gt;REST_HTTP_QUERY (query parameters including bridgeEndpoint=true&lt;/font&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;normal authorization headers if any&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Setting the above values and followed by doing below operation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;.to(&quot;http://dummy?throwExceptionOnFailure=false&amp;amp;hostnameVerifier=ALLOW_ALL&amp;amp;sslContextParameters=#hobsSslContextParameters&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Camel will use actual value from URI, PATH, METHOD and QUERY with dummy before making call.&#160; It is working fine wth 4.6.0&#160; when upgrade it is not working in case QUERY PARAMETER exists.&#160; If QUERY parameter is&#160; not exists then it is working fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please provide your valuable inputs regarding this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17955140" author="JIRAUSER309457" created="Fri, 30 May 2025 08:07:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=davsclaus&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;davsclaus&quot;&gt;davsclaus&lt;/a&gt; ,&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is any workaround ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Siva K Hanumansetti&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17956053" author="JIRAUSER309457" created="Wed, 4 Jun 2025 08:50:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=davsclaus&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;davsclaus&quot;&gt;davsclaus&lt;/a&gt; ,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is any update ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Siva K Hanumansetti&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17956270" author="JIRAUSER309457" created="Thu, 5 Jun 2025 06:39:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=davsclaus&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;davsclaus&quot;&gt;davsclaus&lt;/a&gt; ,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are suspect the usage of BridgeEndpoint=true flag in the query parameter when calling the target system with camel-http.&#160; &#160;Could you please let me know the usage wrt to latest version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Siva K Hanumansetti&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17956562" author="JIRAUSER309457" created="Fri, 6 Jun 2025 11:34:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=davsclaus&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;davsclaus&quot;&gt;davsclaus&lt;/a&gt; ,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Found the issue bridgeEndpoint=true&amp;amp;throwExceptionOnFailure=false not working.&#160; Ignoring the queryparameters which is set in &lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;Exchange.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0000c0&quot;&gt;HTTP_QUERY&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0000c0&quot;&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Please let me know the behavior of bridgeEndpoint=true&amp;amp;throwExceptionOnFailure=false&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Siva K Hanumansetti&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17958216" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2025 06:03:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;bridgeEndpoint and throwExceptionOnFailure are not custom query parameters and not intended for support in HTTP_QUERY. You cannot do that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17958223" author="JIRAUSER309457" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2025 06:27:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is worked in 4.6.0 version.&#160; Now, it is not working&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13076912/13076912_image-2025-06-10-11-55-32-614.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As per the above, we are setting the&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Exchange.CONTENT_TYPE, Exchange.HTTP_METHOD, Exchange.HTTP_URI, Exchange.HTTP_PATH and Exchange.HTTP_QUERY&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and calling to(&quot;http://dummyhost?throwExceptionOnFailure=false&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you have some sample how to use the above with 4.11.0 if any changes happen?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17958620" author="JIRAUSER309457" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2025 08:25:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As per documentation, it is not working.&#160; Please share how to use the same.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17959791" author="JIRAUSER309457" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2025 16:53:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After upgrade from 4.5.0 to 4.11.0 camel version.&#160; &#160;camel-http component,&#160; Query parameters having any special characters $, space, etc.&#160; &#160;Automatically url encoded during the call, due to this communication break.&#160; &#160;Target server is not supported encoded values in the query parameters.&#160; With camel 4.11.0, automatically convert encoded values.&#160; Is there any way to bypass this&#160; (RAW is not working) after upgrade.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17965487" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2025 07:46:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You now give new information about query parameters with special chars.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. I suggest you put together a minimal sample project and attach as .zip to this Jira that shows a single HTTP call with what you do today and you say works for you in older Camel, and then write what you see is changed/different when you upgrade.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Test this sample project with all the camel versions to find out exactly the first version where this is &quot;changed&quot;. This helps us to know what code changes or dependency upgrades may cause this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17980045" author="JIRAUSER309457" created="Tue, 17 Jun 2025 14:56:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&#160;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=davsclaus&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;davsclaus&quot;&gt;davsclaus&lt;/a&gt; ,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Finally found the root cause.&#160; Target system expecting content-type is application/json for the GET operation.&#160; Unfortunately latest version, content-type is filtered when using GET operation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HeaderFilterStrategy to filter this.&#160; But, it is not working.&#160; Is there anyway to don&apos;t filter content-type.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Siva K Hanumansetti&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17981845" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 18 Jun 2025 09:42:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;But the GET request has no payload (body) and as such the content-type header is meaningless. If what you want to tell the server is that you want json as response in the GET call, then use the &quot;Accept&quot; header for that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17981846" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 18 Jun 2025 09:43:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You can try getWithBody=true, and then set an empty &quot;&quot; as body&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17981849" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 18 Jun 2025 09:48:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/commit/c929e96e0a3077c968b183e3d68b3084113124de&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/commit/c929e96e0a3077c968b183e3d68b3084113124de&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
